A new possibility

I also noticed something subtle.

We’ve been exploring domains.

But there is another layer.

Every domain has:

* Physics
* Geometry
* Ecology
* Economics
* Language

For example, cyberspace has:

* physics (latency, bandwidth)
* geometry (network topology)
* ecology (malware, users, bots)
* economics (attention markets)
* language (protocols)

That means every domain isn’t one space.

It’s actually a bundle of interacting spaces.

That suggests the Pantheon could model not just domains, but domain decompositions.

